You are setting `openSession` to `false` at the beginning of every `case` and your `while` loop rightfully stops. Also, you forgot about `break` statements in your `switch`. [More][1] about switch in Java.

Overall, there are several issues in your code.
- `start` should be initialized before the loop
- `productId` and `deliveryAddress` must be declared before the loop
- The whole order placing logic should be a separate choice, because right now it executes when you select `3` and `productId` might not be initialized yet.

You probably want something closer to this:

```Java
        Instant start = Instant.now();
        ArrayList&lt;String&gt; productId = null;
        ArrayList&lt;String&gt; deliveryAddress = null;
        System.out.println(&quot;Session has been opened&quot;);
        while (openSession) {
            System.out.println(&quot;1. Exit&quot;);
            System.out.println(&quot;2. Place item ID you are ordering&quot;);
            System.out.println(&quot;3. Place delivery address&quot;);
            System.out.println(&quot;4. Process order&quot;);
            int userPick = scanner.nextInt();

            switch (userPick) {
                case 1:
                    openSession = false;
                    break;

                case 2:
                    productId = /*init productId*/;
                    break;

                case 3:
                    deliveryAddress = /*init deliveryAddress*/;
                    break;

                case 4:
                    if (deliveryAddress == null) {
                        System.out.println(&quot;Place delivery address first&quot;);
                        break;
                    }
                    if (productId == null) {
                        System.out.println(&quot;Place item ID first&quot;);
                        break;
                    }
                    // Do the business logic, set openSession to false?
                    break;

                default:
                    System.out.println(&quot;Incorrect choice&quot;);
                    break;
            }
        }
        scanner.close();
```

  [1]: https://docs.oracle.com/javase/tutorial/java/nutsandbolts/switch.html

